sec-well-known-intrinsic-objects.title: #sec-well-known-intrinsic-objects Well-Known Intrinsic Objects
sec-well-known-intrinsic-objects.html:
#sec-well-known-intrinsic-objects Well-Known Intrinsic Objects

Well-known intrinsics are built-in objects that are explicitly referenced by the algorithms of this specification and which usually have realm-specific identities. Unless otherwise specified each intrinsic object actually corresponds to a set of similar objects, one per realm.

Within this specification a reference such as %name% means the intrinsic object, associated with the current realm, corresponding to the name. A reference such as %name.a.b% means, as if the "b" property of the "a" property of the intrinsic object %name% was accessed prior to any ECMAScript code being evaluated. Determination of the current realm and its intrinsics is described in #sec-execution-contexts. The well-known intrinsics are listed in #table-well-known-intrinsic-objects.

Note

Additional entries in #table-additional-well-known-intrinsic-objects.
